  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "William announced today that he wants a pet rat for summer, and shockingly, Mom did not say no immediately, which surprised all of us.",
      "zh": "William 今天宣布他暑假想要一隻寵物鼠，令人震驚的是，媽媽居然沒有立刻說不，這讓我們大家都很意外。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The hot weather has clearly affected everyone's mood this week, and even Mom seemed a little more liberal about saying yes to new pets than usual.",
      "zh": "這星期的炎熱天氣顯然影響了大家的心情，就連媽媽對答應養新寵物這件事，似乎都比平常寬鬆一點。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We took a bus to the pet shop, and the motion of the ride made William a little sleepy despite his excitement.",
      "zh": "我們搭公車去寵物店，雖然 William 很興奮，但一路的搖晃還是讓他有點想睡。"
    },
    {
      "en": "At the shop, we had to fill out a small form asking whether we wanted a male or female rat, and William checked \"female\" without hesitation.",
      "zh": "在店裡，我們得填一張小表格，問我們想要公鼠還是母鼠，William 毫不猶豫就勾了「母的」。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He said, in his own words, he preferred a lady rat, since Perry and William are already enough male chaos for one household.",
      "zh": "他用自己的話說，他比較想要一隻女生老鼠，因為 Perry 跟 William 兩個公的在家裡搗蛋已經夠多了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The shop owner, a kind woman named Ms. Tan, said only a small minority of customers ever ask for a pet rat instead of a hamster.",
      "zh": "店主是一位親切的女士，Tan 女士，她說只有一小部分的客人會來要老鼠，而不是要倉鼠。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She said the rat looked a little fat, but that was simply because the shop feeds every animal on a generous daily basis.",
      "zh": "她說那隻老鼠看起來有點胖，但那只是因為店裡每天都很大方地餵食每一隻動物。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William picked her up carefully, and the rat's tiny foot immediately grabbed onto his finger, which made him laugh out loud.",
      "zh": "William 小心翼翼地把牠抱起來，那隻老鼠小小的腳立刻抓住了他的手指，這讓他大笑出聲。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The price was only a few dollars and some cents, which Mom said was surprisingly cheap for how much joy it clearly brought William.",
      "zh": "價格只要幾塊錢加上一點零錢，媽媽說以牠帶給 William 這麼多快樂來看，這價格便宜得讓人驚訝。"
    },
    {
      "en": "On the way out, we passed a drugstore, and Sophia went in quickly to buy some cream for a small cut on her lip.",
      "zh": "出來的路上，我們經過一間藥局，Sophia 快速進去買了一點藥膏，要擦她嘴唇上一個小小的傷口。"
    },
    {
      "en": "While we waited outside, Bernice told us a story from the news about a thief who tried to steal bicycles near the old town gate, but got caught immediately.",
      "zh": "我們在外面等的時候，Bernice 跟我們說了一則新聞，一個小偷想在老城門附近偷腳踏車，結果馬上就被抓到了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William, holding his new rat, said no thief would ever dare steal a pet rat, since apparently nobody wants a rodent that badly.",
      "zh": "抱著新老鼠的 William 說，絕對不會有小偷想偷一隻寵物鼠的，因為顯然沒有人會那麼想要一隻齧齒動物。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Back home, we planted a small seed in the garden as a kind of celebration, watching its future roots begin somewhere under the soil.",
      "zh": "回到家，我們在花園裡種了一顆小種子，算是一種小小的慶祝，看著它未來的根開始在土壤下方生長。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William named his new rat \"Notebook,\" saying it seemed fair, since this whole diary basically started because of a notebook too.",
      "zh": "William 幫他的新老鼠取名叫「筆記本」，他說這樣很公平，畢竟這整本日記說到底也是因為一本筆記本才開始的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "It has been an entire school year since Bernice first said \"diary\" sounded childish, and I still find that a little funny to think about.",
      "zh": "距離 Bernice 第一次說「diary」聽起來很幼稚，已經過了整整一個學年，我現在想起來還是覺得有點好笑。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Thus, this is the last entry of my very first diary, and I plan to keep writing, in one notebook or another, till there is nothing left to say.",
      "zh": "所以，這就是我人生第一本日記的最後一篇，而我打算繼續寫下去，不管是這本還是下一本筆記本，一直寫到再也沒什麼好說的為止。"
    },
    {
      "en": "It has genuinely been a pleasure, dear notebook, and I have a strong feeling this is not actually the end.",
      "zh": "親愛的筆記本，這真的是一段很愉快的旅程，而我強烈感覺這其實根本不是結束。"
    }
  ],
